article.description: — Fletcher Abee's 25 points helped UNC Asheville defeat Wofford 85-82 in overtime on Saturday night in the Northern Classic.
article.headline: UNC Asheville takes down Wofford 85-82 in OT
article.linkText: UNC Asheville takes down Wofford 85-82 in OT
article.story: LAVAL, Quebec -- — Fletcher Abee's 25 points helped UNC Asheville defeat Wofford 85-82 in overtime on Saturday night in the Northern Classic. Nicholas McMullen's layup gave the Bulldogs the lead for good as they closed the extra period with a 6-2 surge. Corey Tripp's four-point play for Wofford with three seconds left in regulation forced overtime tied 79-all. Abee was 5-of-10 shooting, including 4 for 9 from 3-point range, and went 11 for 12 from the line for the Bulldogs (3-3). Jamon Battle scored 17 points and added eight rebounds and five assists. McMullen had 12 points. Tripp led the Terriers (2-4) in scoring, finishing with 21 points, seven rebounds and four assists. Dillon Bailey added 20 points for Wofford. In addition, Kyler Filewich finished with 10 points, 10 rebounds and two blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
